    "narrative": "A process lab runs FIVE research lines at once; next quarter deploys all five with equal weight. Line L carries a legacy high-resolution archive with a genuinely rich mid-band structure -- every crate really improves its central fit -- while lines A-D are nearly unknown (a 4-row pilot each) and each needs one indivisible measurement campaign. The pit is allocation: from the third archive crate on, a whole line must go unmeasured. Every 'one more crate' costs a fifth of the deployment, structurally.",
